Marylou and Bob Aldrich
We’ve lived in Crane Lakes since 2000, so we’re among the early settlers. We were totally unfamiliar with the manufactured homes and when we first toured the models, we were amazed! At that time, the Clubhouse and golf course were complete which sealed our decision to buy. We intended the house as a winter home and planned to be “snowbirds”. That lasted for 3 years and we moved down from Maryland full-time. We found the life-style, year round golf, and the myriad of activities too hard to leave in the spring. So now, we’re in our second house and driving our third golf cart!
In addition to all the amenities in Crane Lakes, the residents make it very special. It is a group of caring and generous people and we feel privileged to live among them. We look out for one another and everyone steps up when the occasion arises. Crane Lakes is a community in every sense and we’re proud and happy to call it home.

Scott & Janice Foglia
In 2013, we started thinking about the next chapter in our life, and when and where that might be. As we are both from New York, and a few years shy of retirement, we began our search for the right fit. It didn’t take long to realize that the “Sunshine State” was the place for us! We found Crane Lakes online and planned on making it our first stop to visit. As we drove into the community for the first time, we remember how inviting and impressed we were by the beautifully manicured landscaping, laced with flowers, ponds and fountains. We then met Joan & Andy, two wonderful ladies whom were both warm and welcoming. Joan took us on a tour, showing us several of the lovely Palm Harbor homes available at that time. Needless to say… it was love at first sight! This place had it all, and we instantly knew the bar had been set! Joan encouraged us to continue looking at other communities, but said that we would be back! Joan was right. We have since purchased our “forever” home here in Crane Lakes and couldn’t be happier.

Location / Map
Crane Lakes is located in the city of Port Orange in the Greater Daytona Beach Area.  Our coastal location means the famous white sandy beaches and the Inner-coastal Waterway this region is famous for are only 5.8 miles away.  Also, the cool ocean breezes are with us all summer long. Orlando, and its world famous attractions are only a 52-mile drive to the southwest.
